07/03/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Albanian Defence Minister Pandeli Majko visits NATO HQ in Brussels on Monday (7 March). 
He will meet with NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer.
In other news, Majko and his Belgian counterpart, Andre Flahaut, signed a memorandum on bilateral co-operation in the military sector during Flahaut's visit to Tirana late last week. 
Flahaut also vowed continued Belgian support for Albania's bid to join NATO and the EU. 
(Albanian News - 05/03/05; NATO Web site - 04/03/05)
